This document explains how we can configure prometheus as a datasource to grafana.

# Configuring Prometheus as a data source
Open Grafana in your web browser (http://publicip:3000).
Click on Configuration menu.
Select Data Sources.
Click on “Add data source”.
Choose “Prometheus” as the type.
Set the appropriate Prometheus server URL, such as http://publicip:9090/
Click Save & Test.

# Verifying the metrics
Select your data source 
At the bottom you will have an explore option
Click it and query for the metrics (eg: up)
